> Point taken, although with the 10 gauge wire I recommended you will have no trouble blowing a 30 amp fuse before the wire is damaged.  50 may be a bit high, I'll admit, but I still think it would work okay.

I run 8-guage wire in my radio installation, along with a 30A breaker.
The radio actually pulls about 20A on transmit, and the 8-ga wire prevents
excessive voltage drop.

